### Cooldown System

#### Overview
A cooldown system prevents a user from performing an action for a certain period of time after they have performed it.

#### Cooldown Structure
```markdown
cooldown: {
  id: string, // unique identifier for the cooldown
  duration: number, // time in milliseconds
  timestamp: number, // timestamp when the cooldown started
}
```

#### Example Usage

```javascript
class CooldownSystem {
  cooldowns = {};

  addCooldown(id, duration) {
    this.cooldowns[id] = {
      duration,
      timestamp: Date.now(),
    };
  }

  checkCooldown(id) {
    const cooldown = this.cooldowns[id];
    if (!cooldown) return false;
    const timeElapsed = Date.now() - cooldown.timestamp;
    return timeElapsed >= cooldown.duration;
